		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Poe Ballantine</strong></span> once took a monastic vow of silence for seven days. Thank-you letters poured in. He is the author of the memoirs <em>Guidelines for Mountain Lion Safety</em> and <em>Love &amp; Terror on the Howling Plains of Nowhere</em>. His newest novel, <em>Whirlaway</em>, is due out on April Fool’s Day 2018. He lives with his wife and son in Chadron, Nebraska.</p><a href="/contributors/poe-ballantine" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;▸</a>		</div>
